citeinfo.title: Virginia Byways and America's Byways in Virginia

pubinfo.publish: ITD / GIS Program, Virginia Department of Transportation

descript.abstract: This layer shows the officially designated Virginia Byways and the America's Byways in Virginia. About 2,500 miles of roads are designated as such. Virginia Byways are marked by special blue signs with red cardinals and dogwood blossoms.
descript.purpose: The Virginia Byways and the America's Byways in Virginia were developed as a GIS layer in the Integrator and on the server for future use on other Virginia Maps.
descript.supplinf:
In accordance with the SERP, VDOT staff will coordinate with VDOT Public Affairs to determine any change in designation when a VDOT project is within 2-miles of a Scenic Road.
This layer was created from an events table using the VDOT LRS.

procstep.procdesc: Made a copy of the byways.mdb from the directory \\Coapp09\gis_development\Scenic_Roads\Meekins_ScenicData. Renamed it byways_original.mdb and place it in the directory \\Coapp09\gis_development\Scenic_Roads\VDOT_AM_ScenBy_LN_6K_0. Copied the Scenic_Byways_Inventory data table from byways_original.mdb, created a new personal geodatabase and copied the Scenic_Byways_Inventory data to the new geodatabase. The new personal geodatabase is named VDOT_AM_ScenBy_LN_6K_0.mdb. Emailed Winky Chenault and asked about an "official" list of the scenic byways. He sent me his list of scenic byways called Virginia Byways.xls. Compared the two datasets to see if they matched and what needed to be altered and added the routes that were not in the original Scenic_Byways_Inventory. Also new routes, which we had notices for, that have been added by the Commonwealth Transportation Board. Performed Add Route Events to map the scenic byways against our current LRS. The current LRS is GIS_DATA.LRS_RTMP located in GIS_DATA.LOCATION_REFERENCING on server coapp10 ArcSDE instance 5151. The scenic byways have a website at http://www.virginiadot.org/infoservice/prog-byways-sites.asp.

New Virginia Byways_Dec2010.xls spreadsheet recieved. Compared to existing events table SCENIC_BYWAYS_INVENTORY. Added newly designated Byways. Created an events feature linking the events table SCENIC_BYWAYS_INVENTORY (htris_route_trim) against the GIS_DATA.LRS_EXPORT/GIS_DATA.SDE_VDOT_RTE_OVERLAP_LRS (ROUTESYSIDSHORT) QA/QC consisted of visually inspecting each route in the feature against the official spreadsheet description.
Scenic_Byways_Inventory Events exported to personal geodatabase feature class
